SUMMARY:CSA Share Fair
DESCRIPTION:Want to Eat More Veggies? Love Local? Try Community Supported Agriculture (CSA)! \nBring the kids and enjoy a family-friendly event filled with fun activities. From farmer matchmaking to a cookbook swap and kid’s scavenger hunt\, this event is all about discovering the benefits of CSA and meeting the people behind the food. Attendees that purchase a CSA share using SNAP get 50% off fruits and vegetables.  \nReal food\, real connections—that’s what CSA is all about. This is a free event.  \nIn a time when food insecurity is on the rise and industrial food systems continue to dominate\, families can join a CSA to make a renewed commitment to eating more veggies\, while strengthening their community\, supporting small farms with sustainable agricultural practices and building local food resilience.  \nNot sure where to start? Every CSA program is different\, and with nearly 100 CSA farms in the region\, PNWCSA can help you find a farm (or farms!) that best fits your eating habits.
URL:https://pdxparent.com/event-single/csa-share-fair/
LOCATION:The Redd on Salmon\, 831 SE Salmon St\, Portland\, OR\, 97214
CATEGORIES:Educational,Indoor,Kids Calendar
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://pdxparent.com/wp-content/uploads/Share_Fair_Art_2026-scaled.png
ORGANIZER;CN="PNWCSA":MAILTO:info@pnwcsa.org
END:VEVENT
